news.title: HDFC witnesses highest ever loan approval; crosses Rs 2 lakh crore in FY22
news.para: HDFC managing director Renu Sud Karnad said, "In over four and half decades, I have not seen a better time for the housing sector than now due to lower interest rates, stable property prices, government's thrust on affordable housing, improved affordability, favourable demographics, increasing urbanisation and rising aspirations".

news.title: To avoid razing 735 buildings, part of Metro Line 5 in Bhiwandi to be underground
news.para: The project is currently estimated at Rs 8,417 crore. The issue was raised by Bhiwandi Samajwadi Party MLA Rais Shaikh on Tuesday. He demanded adequate compensation for commercial shops.

news.title: Haryana: Town planner deputed for illegal colony survey sent back
news.para: Before his temporary deputation to the urban local bodies department in Chandigarh, the official, RS Batth, as DTP (enforcement), was overseeing issues related to Chintels Paradiso and NBCC Green View apartments, apart from doing the coordination for the proposed structural audit of five highrises in Gurgaon.

news.title: Property prices to rise by Rs 400-500 per sq ft in Gujarat
news.para: The decision was taken during the board meeting of Credai Gujarat held in Palanpur on Tuesday. Raw material prices have been the bane of real estate developers for a while now.

news.title: Nine days still to go in March, property tax haul up 25% in Mumbai
news.para: Collection of property tax, currently one of the biggest sources of revenue for the BMC, has touched Rs 4,690.5 crore so far with 9 more days to go for the financial year. Last year around the same time, the BMC had received Rs 3,733 crore.

news.title: Bombay HC notice to partners of realty firm who cheated buyers of Hill View project
news.para: The judges noted that despite recovery certificates obtained from MahaRERA for refund of sale consideration due to delay of several years in constructing their flats, the developer had the “temerity” to tell the court “We have nothing to offer to the flat purchasers.”

news.title: NBFCs seek extension of subsidy under PMAY-CLSS for two years
news.para: The Cabinet had recently approved the extension of the PMAY-Gramin scheme beyond March 2021 to March 2024 to achieve the total target of 29.5 million rural homes.

news.title: Sohna: Cracks on pillars, poor upkeep, allege Breez Global Heights residents
news.para: They said it has only been a few years, but plasters started to peel off and cracks are visible on pillars. The sewage treatment plant (STP) is poorly maintained, there is a lack of security guards, and CCTV cameras and fire alarm system are non-functional, they alleged.

news.title: Gurugram: DC says Green View residents to get refund; NBCC considering it
news.para: Officials said the developer had little choice but to agree to refund the flat owners after a structural audit report by IIT-Roorkee and Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) declared the buildings in the society “unsafe for living”.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing gets committee nod to raise up to Rs 50,000 crore via bonds
news.para: ​As per the existing shareholders' enabling authorisation, valid up to July 28, 2022, the company can raise funds up to Rs 50,000 crore through issuance of secured or unsecured non-convertible debentures (NCDs or bonds) in one or more tranches on a private placement basis.

news.title: Mumbai: Panel for buildings with part or no OC within a month
news.para: Shinde, in a written reply to Prabhu’s query, said there are 728 buildings across Mumbai that have been granted part OC and owe the BMC approximately Rs 1,018 crore in form of various taxes.

news.title: Income tax department searches premises of Hiranandani Group
news.para: ​​On Tuesday, the directorate of I-T investigation, Mumbai, formed teams that arrived at the premises in the morning for the search; it will continue for a few days, it is learnt.

news.title: CREDAI-NCR members plan to stop construction works due to hike in raw material price
news.para: In a statement, CREDAI-NCR said the cost of raw materials has gone up by a weighted average of about 30 to 40 per cent recently while the cost of few items has increased by more than 100 per cent in the last 2 years.

news.title: China Evergrande to resolve $511 million trust loan with state help: Sources
news.para: Under the loan resolution, CITIC will return the land used as collateral to Evergrande, the world's most indebted property developer, who will then pass it on to the Guangzhou city government to put up for sale, the sources said.

news.title: Japan's land prices rebound in 2021 as economy recovers from COVID hit
news.para: Overall, average land prices gained 0.6% in 2021, data from Japan's land ministry showed on Tuesday, following a 0.5% drop in 2020, which marked the first decline in six years.
